  </tr>
</table>
</center>

<p>
<a href="tutorials/paths/PathsTutorial.html">Tutorial on Using and Creating Paths</a>: This tutorial covers the 
feature of BioTapestry that allows you to define named <i>paths</i> through the model hierarchy. You may have 
situations where you have a complex model hierarchy, and you want to be able to easily progress through a series of closely 
related submodels that could be widely dispersed across that hierarchy.  Paths allow you to do this.
</p>

